text: Mount Crysdale, is a ultra-prominent, isolated peak in the Misinchinka Ranges, a subdivision range of the Hart Ranges, within the Northern Rocky Mountains. Officially adopted on 2 September 1954, Mount Crysdale is named after C.R. Crysdale, Chief Engineer, Pacific Great Eastern Railway. == References == Category:Mountains of British Columbia Category:Northern Interior of British Columbia
title: Mount Crysdale
